### Problem

Opening a rust file with the below minimal_init.lua and then running `:= vim.lsp.codelens.refresh()` and `:= vim.lsp.codelens.get()` returns `{}` however if I use the same settings in vscode it correctly displays codelens for implementations and refereneces. I have looked through the help page for lsp for like a week, along with peeking at the implementations of rust-tools.nvim and rustacean.nvim which is a bit beyond me but even with these extensions installed I haven't be able to display codelen's. I feel like I am going crazy. 

